{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "These AI algorithms streamline the assessment of retinal conditions such as DR, AMD, and retinal vein occlusions (RVOs), consequently expediting diagnosis and referrals for positive cases [14,15].",
    "AI-based fundus image analysis allows retinal vessels to be accurately segmented, arterioles and venules to be differentiated, and retinal geometric features to be quantified [15].",
    "This capability enables the identification of systemic vascular disorders like hypertension and diabetes based on retinal microvascular abnormalities [15].",
    "Deep learning algorithms have been devised to measure retinal vessel caliber from fundus photographs autonomously, leveraging previously measured ground truth data for training [15].",
    "Moreover, AI models can directly classify systemic vascular disorders from fundus images without using specific feature extraction [15]."
  ],
